# Comparison Dashboard

## Description

The ComparisonDashboard plugin provides a new type of dashboard that lets you compare report data from different segments.

Reports are displayed side by side in a grid. Each row contains reports of the same type and each column contains reports using the same segment:

![Comparison Dashboard](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PiwikPRO/plugin-ComparisonDashboard/gh-pages/gh-pages/images/comparison_dashboard.png)

Using this layout, you can deepen your understanding of your visitors by finding differences and similarities in your segments.

#### Features

Widgets in the Comparison Dashboard function like normal dashboard widgets, except every change applied to one report is automatically applied to other reports of the same type. This includes changes to the reports themselves, such as changing the number of rows displayed:

![Changed Row Count](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PiwikPRO/plugin-ComparisonDashboard/gh-pages/gh-pages/images/different_limit.png)

And it includes widget operations such as minimisation:

![Minimise Example](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PiwikPRO/plugin-ComparisonDashboard/gh-pages/gh-pages/images/minimise_example.png)

The Comparison Dashboard also provides a new widget operation that will make the y-axis on evolution and bar graphs identical for reports of the same type:

![Identical Scaling](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PiwikPRO/plugin-ComparisonDashboard/gh-pages/gh-pages/images/identical_scaling.png)

This lets you compare graph data with a single glance.

## Manual

#### Comparing Segments

To select segments to compare, use the segment selector located above each dashboard column:

![Segment Selectors](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PiwikPRO/plugin-ComparisonDashboard/gh-pages/gh-pages/images/segment_selectors.png)

You can use these selectors to edit existing segments and create new segments:

![Segment Edit](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PiwikPRO/plugin-ComparisonDashboard/gh-pages/gh-pages/images/segment_edit.png)

#### Managing Widgets

To add a new widget, use the Comparison Dashboard manager:

![Comparison Dashboard Manager](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PiwikPRO/plugin-ComparisonDashboard/gh-pages/gh-pages/images/dashboard_manager.png)

The manager functions just like the normal dashboard manager:

![Open Comparison Dashboard Manager](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PiwikPRO/plugin-ComparisonDashboard/gh-pages/gh-pages/images/dashboard_manager_open.png)

To remove an existing widget, click the **remove icon** located on the top right of each widget:

![Widget Close Icon](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PiwikPRO/plugin-ComparisonDashboard/gh-pages/gh-pages/images/close_icon.png)

#### Identical Y-Axis Scaling

When comparing bar and evolution graphs, it can sometimes be helpful if each individual graph used the same y-axis scale. The Comparison Dashboard lets you apply such a scaling through a widget button:

![Identical Scaling Icon](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PiwikPRO/plugin-ComparisonDashboard/gh-pages/gh-pages/images/identical_scaling_icon.png)

Clicking it will make the y-axis on every graph identical:

![Identical Scaling](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PiwikPRO/plugin-ComparisonDashboard/gh-pages/gh-pages/images/identical_scaling.png)

Clicking it again will undo the changes.

#### Normal Widget Operations

The Comparison Dashboard also supports normal widget operations such as maximisation and minimisation.

**Minimising** a widget will hide the widget\'s contents:

![Minimise Example](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PiwikPRO/plugin-ComparisonDashboard/gh-pages/gh-pages/images/minimise_example.png)

To minimise a widget, click the **minimise icon**:

![Minimise Icon](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PiwikPRO/plugin-ComparisonDashboard/gh-pages/gh-pages/images/maximise_icon.png)

**Refreshing** a widget will reload each report in the row. To refresh a widget, click the **refresh icon**:

![Refresh Icon](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PiwikPRO/plugin-ComparisonDashboard/gh-pages/gh-pages/images/refresh_icon.png)

**Maximising** a widget will create a popup displaying every report in the row:

![Maximise Example](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PiwikPRO/plugin-ComparisonDashboard/gh-pages/gh-pages/images/maximise_example.png)

_Note: You can only edit annotations in the maximise popup._

To maximise a widget, click the **maximise icon**:

![Maximise Icon](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PiwikPRO/plugin-ComparisonDashboard/gh-pages/gh-pages/images/maximise_icon.png)
